                <section class="blade wrapper content">
                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="twelve columns">
                                <h1>Quicktime Plugin Setup</h1>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    The Quicktime Plugin is needed to display the h.264 stream of your INSTAR HD camera in alternative Browsers like Chrome, Safari, Firefox or Opera. Please refer to <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/ActiveX">ActiveX Plugin Installation on Windows</a> if you want to use the Internet Explorer to access your camera.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <h2>Quicktime Setup under Windows</h2>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 1</strong>: Please download the newest version of Quicktime Player from <a href="http://www.apple.com/quicktime/download/">Apple Inc.</a>.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                              <p class="justify">
                                Download the newest version of the full Quicktime player.
                              </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                          <amp-img
                              on="tap:Win_Quicktime_Step1_EN"
                              role="button"
                              tabindex="0"
                              src="/images/Quick_Installation/Win_Quicktime_Step1_EN.jpg" width="700" height="492" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                          </amp-img>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 2</strong>: Please click Run in order to download and start the installation of the Quicktime Player.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 3</strong>: Confirm that you want to install the ClientOCX_Setup.exe ActiveX Control Element by clicking Run in the upcoming window.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <amp-img
                                on="tap:ActiveX_HD_02_Windows_XP_EN"
                                role="button"
                                tabindex="0"
                                src="/images/Quick_Installation/ActiveX_HD_02_Windows_XP_EN.jpg" width="500" height="370" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                            </amp-img>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 4</strong>: After the installation please double click on QuickTime Player to start the program.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 5</strong>: Please select Edit - Preferences and the menu Quicktime Preferences.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <amp-img
                                on="tap:Win_Quicktime_Step3_EN"
                                role="button"
                                tabindex="0"
                                src="/images/Quick_Installation/Win_Quicktime_Step3_EN.jpg" width="700" height="547" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                            </amp-img>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    Navigate to the Quicktime Preferences.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 6</strong>: Please click on Advanced, you should now see the below window.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <amp-img
                                on="tap:Win_Quicktime_Step4_EN"
                                role="button"
                                tabindex="0"
                                src="/images/Quick_Installation/Win_Quicktime_Step4_EN.jpg" width="416" height="558" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                            </amp-img>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                  Click on the Advanced tab.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 7</strong>: Please choose Custom... as the Streaming Transport and select Transport Protocol: HTTP and Port ID: 80 in the next window.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <amp-img
                                on="tap:Win_Quicktime_Step5_EN"
                                role="button"
                                tabindex="0"
                                src="/images/Quick_Installation/Win_Quicktime_Step5_EN.jpg" width="416" height="558" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                            </amp-img>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                  Select the Transport Protocoll HTTP and Port ID 80.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 8</strong>: Please confirm all settings with "OK". Next please open the IP camera in your webbrowser. The picture should now be shown..
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                  <strong>Note 1</strong>: You might have to start the Internet Explorer as Administrator. Just make a right click on the Internet Explorer Symbol in your Start menu and choose "Run as...".
                                </p>
                                <p class="justify">
                                  <strong>Note 2</strong>: If you use a Virus scanner such as <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/Avast">AVAST</a>, <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/Kaspersky_2014">KASPERSKY</a>, <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/AVIRA">AVIRA</a>, <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/F-Secure">F-Secure</a> or <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/AVG">AVG</a> you have to create an exception for the IP address of the camera. The easiest way is to shortly turn of all Internet Security Software in order to check which software is blocking the ActiveX plugin from installation/execution.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <h2>Quicktime Setup under Mac OSX</h2>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 1</strong>: Please open your Finder and select Applications and Utilities as shown below.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                          <amp-img
                              on="tap:MacOS_Quicktime_Step1_EN"
                              role="button"
                              tabindex="0"
                              src="/images/Quick_Installation/MacOS_Quicktime_Step1_EN.jpg" width="700" height="410" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                          </amp-img>
                                <div>
                                    <p class="justify">
                                        Open the Utilities in your Applications folder.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 2</strong>: Inside the folder Utilities please open the program Terminal.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                          <amp-img
                              on="tap:MacOS_Quicktime_Step2_EN"
                              role="button"
                              tabindex="0"
                              src="/images/Quick_Installation/MacOS_Quicktime_Step2_EN.jpg" width="700" height="410" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                          </amp-img>
                                <div>
                                    <p class="justify">
                                        Please start the Terminal from your Utilities folder.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 3</strong>: The Terminal window will open.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                          <amp-img
                              on="tap:MacOS_Quicktime_Step3_EN"
                              role="button"
                              tabindex="0"
                              src="/images/Quick_Installation/MacOS_Quicktime_Step3_EN.jpg" width="586" height="110" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                          </amp-img>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 4</strong>: Please input the following or copy the line into Terminal to make sure it is correct qtdefaults write TransportSettings "HTTP" "80".
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                          <amp-img
                              on="tap:MacOS_Quicktime_Step4_EN"
                              role="button"
                              tabindex="0"
                              src="/images/Quick_Installation/MacOS_Quicktime_Step4_EN.jpg" width="587" height="110" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                          </amp-img>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 5</strong>: Please confirm your input. The following message should be shown in your Terminal window.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                          <amp-img
                              on="tap:MacOS_Quicktime_Step5_EN"
                              role="button"
                              tabindex="0"
                              src="/images/Quick_Installation/MacOS_Quicktime_Step5_EN.jpg" width="587" height="110" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                          </amp-img>
                                <div>
                                    <p class="justify">
                                      Continue the plugin installation.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 6</strong>: Open the IP camera in your web browser. The video should now be shown.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                  <strong>Note 1</strong>: You might have to start the Internet Explorer as Administrator. Just make a right click on the Internet Explorer Symbol in your Start menu and choose "Run as...".
                                </p>
                                <p class="justify">
                                  <strong>Note 2</strong>: If you use a Virus scanner such as <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/Avast">AVAST</a>, <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/Kaspersky_2014">KASPERSKY</a>, <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/AVIRA">AVIRA</a>, <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/F-Secure">F-Secure</a> or <a href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Troubleshooting/AVG">AVG</a> you have to create an exception for the IP address of the camera. The easiest way is to shortly turn of all Internet Security Software in order to check which software is blocking the ActiveX plugin from installation/execution.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                    </div>
